description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced HCPC Registered Specialist Microbiology Biomedical Scientist to work at the Sutton site of The Royal Marsden Hospital. IBMS Specialist Portfolio or demonstrable evidence of equivalent essential. The department runs a diagnostic microbiology service for a specialist cancer hospital, serving a large haemato-oncology transplant unit and busy stem cell laboratory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have recently relocated to new laboratories and are looking to expand our services. The laboratory currently uses bacT/Alert, Vitek 2 and MALDI-ToF in bacteriology and Diasorin Liaison in serology. The department is currently looking to introduce PCR testing of SARS-CoV-2 and other Respiratory Pathogens, experience of this would be an advantage. The department currently operates a weekend and out of hours service for essential and emergency work which the successful applicant would be expected to participate in on a rotational basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gail Gardner, Microbiology Manager, Gail.Gardner@rmh.nhs.uk, 3787&lt;/p&gt;
